CTM Data

Type: object

Common Transmission Model (CTM) Data Schema v0.1

root ctm_version
Type: string

release version of CTM specification

root network
Type: object

structure to hold persistent network data

root network global_params
Type: object

structure to hold global settings for parameters in the network

root network global_params unit_convention
Type: enum (of string)

units used for physical network parameters

Must be one of:

  • "NATURAL_UNITS"
  • "PER_UNIT_COMPONENT_BASE"
  • "PER_UNIT_SYSTEM_BASE"

root network global_params base_mva
Type: number Default: 100.0

[MVA] system-wide apparent power base

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root network global_params bus_ref
Type: object

UID of reference bus of the electrical network

  • Option 1
  • Option 2
root network global_params bus_ref anyOf item 0
Type: integer

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root network global_params bus_ref anyOf item 1
Type: string

root network gen gen items cost_pg_model
Type: enum (of string)

type of generation cost model (i.e., function translating power/energy to money); POLYNOMIAL => costpgparameters is an array with n+1 coefficients for f(x) = a0 + a1 x^1 + ... + an x^n; PIECEWISELINEAR => costpgparameters is a series of values i, fi> and cost (f) should be interpolated linearly in between points; MARGINALCOST => costpgparameters is a series of values i, mi>, where mi is a marginal cost ($/MWh or $/(puh)) and b_i is the amoung of power (MWh or puh) sold at marginal cost m_i

Must be one of:

  • "POLYNOMIAL"
  • "PIECEWISE_LINEAR"
  • "MARGINAL_COST"

root time_series_data
Type: object

structure to contain all time variant data of the system/case. All time series are synchronized to the same timestamps, which should should be stored using Unix time. Structure is quasi-tabular, with uid, name, pathtofile, values, and ext being arrays in the same order of said field. This is done in order to allow for better compression (e.g., using HDF5) for the values field.
